{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in French Saint Martin", "text_new": "{{about|2020 viral pandemic in French Saint Martin|epidemic in Dutch part of the island|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Sint Maarten}}\n{{short description|Ongoing viral pandemic in French Saint Martin}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Saint Martin\n| map1 = File:Saint_Martin-CIA_WFB_Map.png\n| places = \n| legend1 =\n| map2 =   \n| legend2 =\n| map3 =\n| legend3 =\n| disease = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location = [[Collectivity of Saint Martin|Saint Martin]]\n| first_case = \n| arrival_date = 1 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=3|day1=1|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin = \n| confirmed_cases = 38<ref name=\"upd-04-26\"/> (2004-04-26)\n| recovery_cases = 24\n| deaths = 3\n| total_ili =\n| website = [https://www.guadeloupe.ars.sante.fr/coronavirus-informations-et-recommandations-0 guadelope.ars.sante.fr]\n}}\nThe '''[[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|2020 coronavirus pandemic]] in French Saint Martin''' is part of the ongoing global [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|viral pandemic]] of [[coronavirus disease 2019]] (COVID-19), which was confirmed to have reached the [[Overseas collectivity|French overseas collectivity]] of [[Collectivity of Saint Martin|Saint Martin]] on 1 March 2020. The island is split in a Dutch and French part, with the main airport on the Dutch side and the major harbour on the French side. The first positive test was a French couple from Saint Martin who returned from [[France]] via [[collectivity of Saint Barth\u00e9lemy|Saint Barth\u00e9lemy]] on 1 March 2020. They were screened and tested positive on the airport, but are counted on the French count.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.smn-news.com/st-maarten-st-martin-news/34052-state-of-affairs-on-st-maarten-regarding-the-covid-19.html |title=St. Martin News Network \u2013 State of Affairs on St. Maarten regarding the COVID-19. |website=smn-news.com|access-date=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n==Timeline==\n{{Medical cases chart\n|numwidth=wmd\n\n|disease=COVID-19\n|location=Saint Martin\n|outbreak=2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic\n\n|togglesbar=\n<div class=\"nomobile\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n{{Medical cases chart/Month toggle button|mar}}\n{{Medical cases chart/Month toggle button|apr}}\n<span class=\"mw-collapsible mw-customtoggle-l15 mw-customtoggle-mar-l15 mw-customtoggle-apr-l15 mw-collapsed\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-l15\" style=\"padding:0 8px\">Last 15 days</span>\n<span class=\"mw-collapsible mw-customtoggle-l15 mw-customtoggle-mar-l15 mw-customtoggle-apr-l15\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-l15\" style=\"border:2px solid lightblue; padding:0 8px\">Last 15 days</span>\n</div>\n\n|collapsible=y\n|data=\n<!--date;deaths;recoveries;total_cases;;;total_cases;+%;-->\n2020-03-01; 0;  0;  2;;;  2<ref name=\"first\"/>;\n;           0;  0;  2;;;  2;collapsed=y;id=mar\n2020-03-15; 0;  2;  2;;;  2<ref name=\"outremer\">{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/longs-formats-carte-coronavirus-combien-cas-outre-mer-807779.html|title=Coronovirus Nombre de cas confirm\u00e9s en Outre-mer|language=fr|website=Outre-mer la 1\u00e8re|access-date=22 April 2020}}</ref>;=\n2020-03-16; 0;  2;  2;;;  2;\n2020-03-17; 0;  2;  3;;;  3<ref name=\"outremer\"/>;+50%\n2020-03-18; 0;  2;  4;;;  4<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guadeloupe/saint-martin/saint-martin-heure-du-confinement-814070.html|title=CORONAVIRUS : Saint-Martin, o\u00f9 2 patients sont hospitalis\u00e9s, \u00e0 l'heure du confinement.|access-date=22 April 2020|website=Guadeloupe la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>;+33%\n;           0;  2;  4;;;  4;collapsed=y;id=mar\n2020-03-21; 0;  2;  5;;;  5<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/one-new-case-in-st-martin-as-of-saturday-ars-confirms|title=One new case in St. Martin as of Saturday, ARS confirms |website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=22 April 2020}}</ref>;+25%\n2020-03-22; 0;  2;  5;;;  5;=\n2020-03-23; 0;  2;  8;;;  8<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guadeloupe/coronavirus-pres-650-cas-confirmes-recenses-region-caraibe-815150.html|title=Coronavirus : Pr\u00e8s de 650 cas confirm\u00e9s recens\u00e9s dans la grande r\u00e9gion Cara\u00efbe|access-date=22 April 2020|website=Guadeloupe la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>;+60%\n2020-03-24; 0;  2;  8;;;  8;=\n2020-03-25; 0;  2; 11;;; 11<ref name=\"outremer\"/>;+38%\n2020-03-26; 0;  2; 12;;; 12<ref name=\"local\"/>;+9.1%\n2020-03-27; 1;  2; 13;;; 13<ref name=\"upd-03-27\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/covid-19-cases-on-french-side-up-to-11-as-of-friday|title=COVID-19 cases on French side up to 11 as of Friday |website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=22 April 2020}}</ref>;+8.3%\n2020-03-28; 1;  2; 14;;; 14<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guadeloupe/deux-cas-supplementaires-covid-19-iles-du-nord-20-817302.html|title=Deux cas suppl\u00e9mentaires de Covid-19 dans les \u00eeles du Nord, 20 en tout.|access-date=22 April 2020|website=Guadeloupe la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>;+7.7%\n2020-03-29; 1;  2; 18;;; 18<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/st-martin-records-a-sharp-rise-in-covid-19-cases-and-first-death|title=St. Martin records a sharp rise in COVID-19 cases, and first death|website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=22 April 2020}}</ref>;+29%\n2020-03-30; 2;  2; 18;;; 18<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/ars-announces-second-death-from-covid-19-in-st-martin|title=ARS announces second death from COVID-19 in St. Martin |access-date=22 April 2020|website=The Daily Herald.sx}}</ref>;=\n2020-03-31; 2;  2; 21;;; 21<ref name=\"news-03-31\">{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guadeloupe/coronavirus-21-cas-confirmes-saint-martin-3-plus-24-heures-818320.html|title=Coronavirus : 21 cas confirm\u00e9s \u00e0 Saint-Martin, 3 de plus en 24 heures|access-date=22 April 2020|website=Guadeloupe la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>;+17%\n2020-04-01; 2;  5; 22;;; 22<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guadeloupe/coronavirus-l-epidemie-poursuit-sa-progression-a-saint-martin-et-en-guadeloupe-818716.html|title=Coronavirus : l'\u00e9pid\u00e9mie poursuit sa progression \u00e0 Saint-Martin|access-date=22 April 2020|website=Guadeloupe la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>;+4.8%\n2020-04-02; 2;  5; 22;;; 22<ref name=\"outremer\"/>;=\n2020-04-03; 2;  5; 24;;; 24<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guadeloupe/coronavirus-a-saint-martin-2-nouveaux-cas-confirmes-et-2-rapatriements-819480.html|title=Coronavirus : A Saint-Martin, 2 nouveaux cas confirm\u00e9s et 2 rapatriements|language=fr|access-date=22 April 2020|website=Guadeloupe la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>;+9.1%\n2020-04-04; 2; 11; 29;;; 29<ref name=\"outremer\"/>;+21%\n2020-04-05; 2; 11; 31;;; 31<ref name=\"outremer\"/>{{efn|''The Daily Herald'' reports 19 active cases,<ref name=\"herald_april5\"/> however the number of active cases on 5 April is 18 according to ''Outre-mer la 1\u00e8re''.<ref name=\"outremer\" />}};+6.9%\n;           2; 11; 31;;; 31;collapsed=y;id=apr\n2020-04-08; 2; 11; 32;;; 32<ref name=\"outremer\"/>;+3.2%\n;           2; 11; 32;;; 32;collapsed=y;id=apr\n2020-04-11; 2; 11; 33;;; 33<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guadeloupe/coronavirus-1-cas-de-plus-a-saint-martin-porte-a-33-le-nombre-total-de-cas-dans-l-ile-822112.html|title=Coronavirus : 1 cas de plus \u00e0 Saint-Martin porte \u00e0 33 le nombre total de cas dans l'\u00eele|language=fr|access-date=22 April 2020|website=Guadeloupe la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>;+3.1%\n2020-04-12; 2; 11; 33;;; 33<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guadeloupe/coronavirus-toujours-33-cas-confirmes-a-saint-martin-mais-une-hospitalisation-supplementaire-822398.html|title=Coronavirus : toujours 33 cas confirm\u00e9s \u00e0 Saint-Martin mais une hospitalisation suppl\u00e9mentaire|language=fr|access-date=22 April 2020|website=Guadeloupe la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>;=\n2020-04-13; 2; 11; 34;;; 34<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guadeloupe/coronavirus-1-cas-de-plus-a-saint-martin-porte-a-34-le-nombre-total-de-cas-confirmes-822678.html|title=Coronavirus : 1 cas de plus \u00e0 Saint-Martin porte \u00e0 34 le nombre total de cas confirm\u00e9s|language=fr|access-date=22 April 2020|website=Guadeloupe la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>;+3.0%\n2020-04-14; 2; 11; 35;;; 35<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/guadeloupe/coronavirus-1-cas-de-plus-a-saint-martin-porte-a-35-le-nombre-total-de-cas-confirmes-822982.html|title=Coronavirus : 1 cas de plus \u00e0 Saint-Martin porte \u00e0 35 le nombre total de cas confirm\u00e9s|language=fr|access-date=22 April 2020|website=Guadeloupe la 1\u00e8re}}</ref>;+2.9%\n;           2; 11; 35;;; 35;collapsed=y;id=apr\n2020-04-17; 2; 17; 37;;; 37<ref name=\"ars\">{{Cite web|title=Coronavirus : informations et recommandations|url=https://www.guadeloupe.ars.sante.fr/coronavirus-informations-et-recommandations-0|access-date=22 April 2020|website=gaudeloupe.ars.sante.fr|language=fr}}</ref>;+5.7%\n;           2; 17; 37;;; 37;collapsed=y;id=apr\n2020-04-21; 2; 17; 38;;; 38<ref name=\"ars\"/>;+2.7%\n2020-04-22; 2; 18; 38;;; 38<ref name=\"upd-04-22\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.guadeloupe.ars.sante.fr/system/files/2020-04/22042020%20iles%20du%20nord%20point%20de%20situation%20Coronavirus.pdf|title=Bulletin n\u00b049 Information \u00ab coronavirus \u00bb Point de situation au 22 avril 2020|language=fr|website=gaudeloupe.ars.sante.fr|access-date=23 April 2020}}</ref>;=\n2020-04-23; 3; 20; 38;;; 38<ref name=\"upd-04-23\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.guadeloupe.ars.sante.fr/system/files/2020-04/22042020%20iles%20du%20nord%20point%20de%20situation%20Coronavirus.pdf|title=Bulletin n\u00b049 Information \u00ab coronavirus \u00bb Point de situation au 22 avril 2020|language=fr|website=gaudeloupe.ars.sante.fr|access-date=24 April 2020}}</ref>;=\n2020-04-24; 3; 24; 38;;; 38<ref name=\"upd-04-24\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.guadeloupe.ars.sante.fr/system/files/2020-04/23042020%20iles%20du%20nord%20point%20de%20situation%20Coronavirus.pdf|title=Bulletin n\u00b050 Information \u00ab coronavirus \u00bb Point de situation au 23 avril 2020|language=fr|website=gaudeloupe.ars.sante.fr|access-date=25 April 2020}}</ref>;=\n2020-04-25; 3; 24; 38;;; 38<ref name=\"upd-04-25\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.guadeloupe.ars.sante.fr/system/files/2020-04/25042020%20iles%20du%20nord%20point%20de%20situation%20Coronavirus.pdf|title=Bulletin n\u00b052Information \u00ab coronavirus \u00bbPoint de situation au 25 avril 2020|language=fr|website=gaudeloupe.ars.sante.fr|access-date=25 April 2020}}</ref>;=\n2020-04-26; 3; 24; 38;;; 38<ref name=\"upd-04-26\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.guadeloupe.ars.sante.fr/system/files/2020-04/25042020%20iles%20du%20nord%20point%20de%20situation%20Coronavirus.pdf|title=Bulletin n\u00b052 Information \u00ab coronavirus \u00bb Point de situation au 25 avril 2020|language=fr|website=gaudeloupe.ars.sante.fr|access-date=26 April 2020}}</ref>;=\n\n|caption=Data sourced from [https://www.guadeloupe.ars.sante.fr/coronavirus-informations-et-recommandations-0 guadelope.ars.sante.fr]\n}}\n===March===\nOn 1 March, a couple from the French part of [[Saint Martin]] island were diagnosed with [[COVID-19]]. Their son, who lives on the neighbouring island of [[Saint Barth\u00e9lemy]], also tested positive.<ref name=\"first\">{{Cite web|url=http://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/polynesie/coronavirus-premiers-cas-confirmes-outre-mer-saint-martin-saint-barth-805865.html|title=Coronavirus : premiers cas confirm\u00e9s en Outre-mer, \u00e0 Saint-Martin et Saint-Barth|website=Polyn\u00e9sie la 1\u00e8re|language=fr-FR|access-date=2020-03-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302172416/https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/polynesie/coronavirus-premiers-cas-confirmes-outre-mer-saint-martin-saint-barth-805865.html|archive-date=2 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 March, the following measures were announced by the President [[Emmanuel Macron|Macron]]: It is prohibited to leave the house except for essential journeys, all restaurants and bars have to close, all schools have to close, and all gatherings are banned. <ref name=\"measures\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-51892477|title=Coronavirus: Spain and France announce sweeping restrictions|work=BBC News|date=15 March 2020|accessdate=15 March 2020}}</ref> Prefect [[Sylvie Feucher]] has adopted the same measures on Saint Martin. <ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/all-french-side-restaurants-bars-and-cafes-to-close-for-next-15-days|title=All French-side restaurants, bars and caf\u00e9s to close for next 15 days |website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, a fourth case was announced. The patient had returned from a trip to [[Paris]]. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/covid-19-cases-up-to-2-on-french-side|title=COVID-19 cases up to 2 on French side |website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n<br>\nNon-residents can no longer enter the island via the airport. After 22 March, nobody is allowed to enter the island. <ref name=\"airport\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/non-residents-can-t-enter-st-maarten|title=Non-residents can\u2019t enter St. Maarten|access-date=22 April 2020|website=The Daily Herald.sx}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 March, ARS announced that the [[intensive care|ICU]] capacity in [[Guadeloupe]] had been increased to 33 beds. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/ars-ramps-up-supply-of-beds-ventilators-for-guadeloupe-st-martin-and-st-barths|title=ARS ramps up supply of beds, ventilators, for Guadeloupe, St. Martin and St. Barths|website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=22 April 2020}}</ref> Specialized care has to be performed in Guadeloupe.\n\nOn 24 March, the confinement orders have been strengthened: people may only leave their house for essential travel; markets are closed; gatherings are forbidden; non-essential businesses should close. <ref name=\"extra_measures\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/french-pm-revises-confinement-measures-effective-march-24|title=French PM revises confinement measures effective March 24 |website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 March, The collectivity's first death was recorded, after a 61-year-old died from breathing complications following a car accident. The patient tested positive for COVID-19 the following day.<ref name=\":33\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.loopnewsbarbados.com/content/saint-martin-records-first-coronavirus-death-3|title=Saint Martin records first coronavirus death|website=Loop News Barbados|language=en-EN|access-date=2020-03-31|url-status=live}}</ref> On the same day it was announced that last two cases were locally infected and not imported. <ref name=\"local\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/update-new-covid-19-case-on-thursday-ars-confirms|title=Update new Covid-19 case on Thursday ARS confirms|website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 March, another case had been discovered bringing the total to 13. An American patient has been transferred to [[Miami]].<ref name=\"upd-03-27\"/>\n\nOn 28 March, a support package for businesses was announced. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/french-state-implements-immediate-aid-measures-to-support-economy-businesses|title=French State implements immediate aid measures to support economy, businesses |website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 29 March, the border between the Dutch and French side was closed, and is jointly patrolled with the Sint Maarten government. <ref name=\"travel_restriction\">{{cite web |url=http://www.sintmaartengov.org/PressReleases/Pages/Prime-Minister-Chair-of-the-EOC-Silveria-Jacobs-Updates-on-COVID19-Developments-MARCH-29-2020.aspx |title= Prime Minister & Chair of the EOC Silveria Jacobs Updates on COVID-19 Developments MARCH 29, 2020 |work= Government of St Maarten}}</ref> On 6 April, the minor roads were physically blocked to prevent crossings. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/barricaded|title=Barricaded |website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 March, the second death was announced. It concerned a 80-year old man. <ref name=\"outremer\"/>\n\n===April===\nOn 5 April, two more cases were announced bringing the total active cases to 19. One of the cases is an inhabitant of [[Sandy Ground, Anguilla|Sandy Ground]], [[Anguilla]] who was evacuated to Guadeloupe. Prefect Sylvie Feucher has ordered 16 more gendarmes. <ref name=\"herald_april5\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/covid-19-active-cases-rise-to-19-as-gendarme-reinforcements-arrive|title=COVID-19 active cases rise to 19 as Gendarme reinforcements arrive |website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 April, the Pr\u00e9fecture asked people to stay at home during [[Easter]]. Unlike the Dutch side and other islands no curfew will be instituted, but anybody discovered outside without reason will be fined.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/prefecture-reminds-citizens-to-stay-home-on-easter-weekend|title=Pr\u00e9fecture reminds citizens to stay home on Easter weekend|website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 April, the 33rd Marine Infantry Regiment arrived in [[Marigot, Saint Martin|Marigot]] to provide logical support. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/gibbs-welcomes-army-units-from-33rd-marine-infantry-regiment-to-st-martin|title=Gibbs welcomes army units from 33rd Marine Infantry Regiment to St. Martin |website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=22 April 2020}}</ref> A coordination point in [[Martinique]] was setup to coordinate the border controls of the [[Dutch Caribbean]], France and [[United Kingdom]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.infobonaire.com/navy-ship-zr-ms-karel-doorman-to-the-caribbean/|title=Navy ship Zr Ms Karel Doorman to the Caribbean|access-date=17 April 2020|website=The Bonaire Information Site|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200415075252/https://www.infobonaire.com/navy-ship-zr-ms-karel-doorman-to-the-caribbean/|archive-date=15 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 April, Prime Minister [[Silveria Jacobs]] of Sint Maarten announced that the recent death was a Dutch citizen who was being treated on the French side. Last week he was flown to [[Guadelope]] for critical care, however as a Dutch citizen he will be removed from the French Saint Martin count and added to the Dutch Sint Maarten count. <ref name=\"tenth_death\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/three-more-positive-cases-1-more-covid-19-death-for-st-maarten |title=Three more positive cases, 1 more COVID-19 death for St. Maarten|website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 April, President [[Daniel Gibbs]] said that he does not expect the schools to open on 11 May as announced by [[Emmanuel Macron|Macron]]: \u201cWe will not put our children, the educational community and all families of this island in danger because of hasty decisions.\u201d <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/collectivite-does-not-envisage-opening-schools-any-time-soon|title=Collectivit\u00e9 does not envisage opening schools any time soon |website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n<br>\nThe neighbouring island of [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Saint Barth\u00e9lemy|Saint Barth\u00e9lemy]] was declared virus free. <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.guadeloupe.ars.sante.fr/system/files/2020-04/21042020%20st%20martin%20point%20de%20situation%20Coronavirus.pdf |title=Point de situation au 21 avril 2020 |work=Bulletin de l'ARS |date=21 April 2020 |access-date=21 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 April, the third death was announced. The deceased was a 76-year-old man.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/st-martin-records-third-death-from-covid-19|title=St. Martin records third death from COVID-19|website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=24 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 April, [[Air Cara\u00efbes]] announced that flights between Saint Martin ([[Grand Case-Esp\u00e9rance Airport]] not [[Princess Juliana International Airport]]), Saint Barth\u00e9lemy, and Gaudeloupe will be resuming as of today.<ref name=\"flight\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/air-caraibes-resuming-flights-to-guadeloupe-as-of-april-24|title=Air Cara\u00efbes resuming flights to Guadeloupe as of April 24|website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=24 April 2020}}</ref>\n<br>\nThe Pr\u00e9fecture disclosed that 400 tourists have been repatriated up to now. There are still about 50 people stranded, but only those with an urgent reason will be repatriated.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/400-stranded-tourists-taken-into-care-by-the-prefecture|title=400 stranded tourists taken into care by the Pr\u00e9fecture |website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=24 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===May===\nFrom 4 May onwards, the Louis-Constant Fleming Hospital together with the [[Red Cross]] will start screening and testing the population starting with the French Quarter, [[Sandy Ground, Saint Martin|Sandy Ground]] and St. James.<ref>{{Cite news|title=COVID-19 tests to begin May 4 in three districts |url=https://www.thedailyherald.sx/islands/covid-19-tests-to-begin-may-4-in-three-districts|website=The Daily Herald.sx|access-date=27 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Preventive measures==\n* Airport and ports are closed.<ref name=\"airport\"/><ref name=\"measures\"/> Local flights have resumed on [[Grand Case]].<ref name=\"flight\"/>\n* The border between the Dutch and French side is closed. <ref name=\"travel_restriction\"/>\n* All restaurants and bars are closed, all schools are closed, and all gatherings are banned. <ref name=\"measures\"/>\n* All non-essential businesses are closed. <ref name=\"extra_measures\"/>\n* It is prohibited to leave the house except for essential journeys. <ref name=\"measures\"/>\n\n<div style=\"clear:both;\"> </div>\n==Statistics==\nChronology of the number of active cases\n{{Graph:Chart\n| type = line\n| linewidth = 1\n| showSymbols = 1\n| yType= integer\n| width = 600\n| colors = #ff6347, cyan, black\n| xAxisTitle = Date\n| xAxisAngle = -40\n| xType = date\n| xAxisFormat = %e %b\n| x = 29 February 2020, 1 March 2020, 2 March 2020, 3 March 2020, 4 March 2020, 5 March 2020, 6 March 2020, 7 March 2020, 8 March 2020, 9 March 2020, 10 March 2020, 11 March 2020, 12 March 2020, 13 March 2020, 14 March 2020, 15 March 2020, 16 March 2020, 17 March 2020, 18 March 2020, 19 March 2020, 20 March 2020, 21 March 2020, 22 March 2020, 23 March 2020, 24 March 2020, 25 March 2020, 26 March 2020, 27 March 2020, 28 March 2020, 29 March 2020, 30 March 2020, 31 March 2020, 1 April 2020, 2 April 2020, 3 April 2020, 4 April 2020, 5 April 2020, 6 April 2020, 7 April 2020, 8 April 2020, 9 April 2020, 10 April 2020, 11 April 2020, 12 April 2020, 13 April 2020, 14 April 2020, 15 April 2020, 16 April 2020, 17 April 2020, 18 April 2020, 19 April